His Honour considered the relationship between the concept of a particular social group and a policy applied generally and said (at 243):

 "Rather, the persecution is carried out in the enforcement of a policy which applies generally.

In dealing with coercive measures, the Tribunal referred to the following: 
(1) A statement by the United States of America Department of State in 1999;

(2) A Canadian report dated 2000;

(3) Reports prepared by the Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade in 2004;

(4) A news article, another Canadian report and other reports of the Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade.
